  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Developing a HIV and AIDS response for the Colombian Catholic Church</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">One of CAFOD&apos;s principal partners in Colombia, SNPS is the social department of the Colombian Church and a member of the Caritas Network.   SNPS coordinates a network of offices throughout Colombia that seek to promote peace and reconciliation, and defend human rights. 

Colombia is a country that has been ravaged by internal conflict for over 40 years and as a result over three million people have been displaced. Currently the HIV prevalence in Colombia is low (0.6% of the national adult population) and there is very little evidence of AIDS-related illnesses in the population generally, although some evidence of chronic sickness, increased TB etc is apparent among more vulnerable populations. However it is believed that real figures must be higher due to the numerous factors increasing people&#x2019;s vulnerability such as poverty, unemployment, trafficking, sexual violence, militarisation, low awareness, stigma, discrimination and gender inequality.

As a result of this context, CAFOD ran a workshop on HIV and AIDS mainstreaming in 2008 for Pastoral Social staff. SNPS would like to take this work forward and submitted a proposal to CAFOD to develop a HIV strategy for SNPS (Cycle 1). As part of Cycle 2, SNPS are looking to mainstream this HIV strategy into the work of the Colombian Catholic Church and other projects and programmes of SNPS through capacity building and campaigns.</narrative>
  </description>
